# 4. OWN

[Amia]: <Yawn... I don't think I've got any more in me today. I'm gonna log off.>
[Yuki]: <Okay. Goodnight, Amia.>
[Enanan]: <In that case, I'll also... Oh, that reminds me. I had something I wanted to ask you guys.>
[Enanan]: <Have you heard of OWN?>
[K]: <OWN?>
[Amia]: <Yeah! I've heard of them! A lot of people are talking about 'em right now!>
[Yuki]: <Really? What is it?>
[Amia]: <It's another creator who makes music like us! They showed up out of the blue about two weeks ago. Every song they've posted has gotten over 200,000 views.>
[Yuki]: <Over 200,000? That's impressive for someone who just started.>
[K]: <Never heard of them. How did they get so popular?>
[Amia]: <I'm not surprised. I didn't know about them either until yesterday. One of my die-hard music buddies told me about them.>
[Enanan]: <I'll send you the URL so you can check 'em out. I'm sure you two will be surprised. Their songs are kinda overwhelming.>
[Yuki]: <Are they really that good?>
[Enanan]: <Yeah. It's hard to describe, but it felt like the first time I heard one of K's songs. Like they've taken something that's too hard to put into words and given it form.>
[Enanan]: <Unlike K's songs, though, OWN's are really cold.>
[K]: <Cold?>
[Enanan]: <I don't know if I'm explaining it very well, but even though your songs give off a dark, sad feeling, they also have a sense of warmth to them.>
[Enanan]: <OWN's don't have that at all. They're cold all the way through. It feels like they're rejecting anything and everything.>
[Enanan]: <But that's what gives them their appeal. To be honest, it's a little scary, but I really like them.>
[Amia]: <I totally get it. They have that kind of sharp tone that feels like it's cutting into your soul. I wonder what kind of person you have to be to make songs like that.>
[Enanan]: <No idea. I'm curious, but I also don't think I want to know.>
[Enanan]: <If only my drawings could be that amazing, too...>
[K]: <Enanan?>
[Enanan]: <Oh, sorry. It's nothing. Forget I said anything.>
[Yuki]: <I think your artwork is plenty amazing, Enanan.>
[Enanan]: <Huh?>
[Yuki]: <You always manage to capture the feel of K's songs perfectly. I was really surprised at how good your last illustration was.>
[Yuki]: <It felt delicate and gentle, but also a little sad. I thought it was wonderful.>
[Enanan]: <Really?>
[Yuki]: <Yeah. I really like your art.>
[Enanan]: <Thanks, Yuki...>
[Amia]: <*Yawn*...>
[Amia]: <I'm starting to pass out here. Time to get some sleep.>
[Enanan]: <I should get to sleep, too. Talk to you tomorrow.>
[K]: <OWN...>
[K]: <Here they are. Looks like they've already got four songs.>
[Yuki]: <Yeah. I wonder what they're like. Why don't we give them a listen?>
[K]: <This song...>
[K]: (It's like I can hear them screaming...)
[K]: (It feels like they're all alone, drowning in a sea of despair.)
[Yuki]: <Th-This sure is something else...>
[K]: <Yeah.>
[K]: (But this sound... This feeling... I feel like I've heard it before...)
[K]: <Ah...>
[Yuki]: <Just listening to the one song is kind of exhausting. I think I get what Enanan meant by it being overwhelming.>
[Yuki]: <What do you want to do, K? Should we listen to another...>
[K]: <Hey, Yuki?>
[K]: <Did you make this?>
[Yuki]: <What?>
[K]: <It reminds me of the songs you used to write.>
[Yuki]: <.....>
[Yuki]: <You think so?>
[Yuki]: <I don't really see it. Besides, I wouldn't know how to arrange sounds like these.>
[Yuki]: <I couldn't come up with such heavy lyrics, either.>
[K]: <It's true, the lyrics are completely different than what you normally write, but still...>
[K]: <This really wasn't you?>
[Yuki]: <Hehe. You doubting me like this actually makes me more confident in my own work.>
[Yuki]: <It's hard to believe I'd be mistaken for someone so popular.>
[K]: <Sorry...>
[Yuki]: <Don't worry about it. I'm just surprised you remembered my old songs. It's been over a year since I wrote those.>
[K]: <Yeah, they really left an impression.>
[Yuki]: <I see. It's already been quite a while since we started chatting like this, hasn't it?>
[Yuki]: <I was really surprised to get a DM asking to make songs together from an account with zero followers and no profile picture.>
[Yuki]: <I thought it was spam at first.>
[K]: <After listening to your music, I knew I had to contact you right away, so I created an account on the spot.>
[Yuki]: <It's fine. I'm happy you did.>
[Yuki]: <Time sure has flown, though. First Enanan joined, then Amia, and before long we even came up with a name.>
[Yuki]: <I never imagined I'd be making songs with other people like this a year ago.>
[Yuki]: <So thanks for the invite, K.>
[K]: <It was nothing...>
[K]: <.....>
[K]: <Hey, Yuki? Why did you agree to work with me?>
[Yuki]: <What?>
[Yuki]: <I guess because it sounded fun? It's not every day you get the chance to make songs with a group.>
[Yuki]: <That and because I was really impressed the first time I listened to your songs. At the time, I...>
[Yuki]: <I felt like your song saved me.>
[K]: <Huh? Saved?>
[Yuki]: <Huh? S-Sorry, that sounded strange, didn't it? Maybe we should get back to work. It'll be morning soon.>
[K]: <O-Okay...>
[Yuki]: <Alright, I'll talk to you later, then.>
Kanade: So...
Kanade: I actually managed to save someone with my songs.
Kanade: I'm so glad.
Mafuyu: .....
Mafuyu: I was saved?
Mafuyu: What was I thinking?
Mafuyu: OWN...
Comment: <Whenever I listen to OWN's music, I feel like I'm being sucked into some other place.>
Comment: <There's something wrong with whoever made these. I wonder who it is.>
Comment: <Listening to these makes me want to disappear, but I just can't seem to stop. So strange.>
Mafuyu: Lame...
Mafuyu: Even after making all these, I still can't find what I'm looking for.
Mafuyu: If that's the case, then...
